text.__SUMMARY__: Conus paranobilis is an extinct species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails, cone shells or cones.It is the type species of the extinct family Herndliconus Petuch & Drolshagen, 2015
text.Distribution: This marine species is only known as a fossil from the Okeechobean Sea (Pliocene, Pleistocene).
text.References: Petuch E.J., Drolshagen M. & Herndl G. (2015). Cone shells of the Okeechobean Sea (Pliocene, Pleistocene). Harxheim: Conchbooks. 179 pp. page(s): 60
